# Force LF line endings for shell scripts. WSL bash silently treats
# \r as part of the token, corrupting `if`/`fi`/`then` and producing
# "syntax error: unexpected end of file from 'if' command" when a
# script is committed on Windows with core.autocrlf=true and ends up
# on the WSL side as CRLF. Keep shell scripts LF on disk too.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf

# Manifest + YAML: keep LF so the line-ending churn doesn't pollute
# future diffs (this repo had a 3000-line spurious diff once because
# HEAD was LF and on-disk was CRLF).
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf